description: For sale: $294,600. Welcome Home! Cared for by the current owner for 47 years! The main-level of the home features a beautiful living room with a southern exposure and wood burning fireplace. The semi-formal dining area and 3 season porch are just steps from the open kitchen spaces. A few steps down the hall leads you to the main floor bath and the 3 bedrooms. Bedrooms 2 & 3 feature southern exposures and the original hardwood flooring that extends throughout the hall beneath the carpeting. The master bedroom is spacious and features a full en-suite bath. The lower level features a large L shaped family room with a gas fireplace and walk-out to the backyard and large concrete patio. On the lower level you will also find a large laundry/mechanical room in addition to the lower level bath. Don't forget the large 2 car garage with a separate bonus storage area! This centrally located Roseville home is near schools, shopping, entertainment, dining, transportation and recreation activities!

For sale: $499,900. Gorgeous to be built 4 Bedroom, 3 Bath, 3 Car two story. Quality construction and Finishes throughout--Lots of windows. Convenient location adjacent to newer construction. Plan can change to suit buyers.

description:
Recently sold: $285,000. Charming 1.5 story in the heart of Roseville, just minutes walk from shopping and eating. Huge master bedroom up with 2 more bedrooms on main. Freshly redone orig hardwood floors, brand new carpet downstairs, tiled kitchen. New roof 2014, new windows 2012, new furnace 2016, new water heater 2017. Fully fenced yard. Mature trees. Extra deep oversized 2 car garage. 
Directions 35W S to 36. Take the Hamline exit, home is just west of the Hamline/County B intersection.  2 buildings down from Dave's Auto Care.

Recently sold: $325,000. Fantastic rambler on a non-through street in a terrific Roseville location. Nice large lot in back, great for grilling and entertaining, backs up to city park land for added privacy. Well-built and classic style - update to your specific taste, make it modern or embrace the mid-century aspect. Main level features 3 bedrooms, full bath, large living room with formal dining and huge family room + a good-sized kitchen with casual dining attached with Ample workspace. - all appliances stay. Den and recreation room in the lower level with access to mechanicals, laundry and a 3/4 bath. Updated Anderson windows throughout, furnace and water heater updated in 2018. 2 car attached garage with plenty of room + a concrete driveway. Walk or bike to schools, restaurants, shopping and parks. Home pre-inspected and home warranty provided.

description: Recently sold: $244,000. Have you been looking for that perfect 1st home for you and your family? Then come take a look at this one on 1321 Rose Place in the heart of Roseville right off Hamline Ave. You will find a home that is move in ready and updated to boot. The hardwood floors have all just been refinished, the kitchen counter was replaced. The whole upper level was repainted, hardwood floors refinished and new carpet was installed in the master BR. This 4 bed, 2 bath Roseville home is just minutes from Rosedale, Hwy 36, parks, lakes and more! The living room is spacious and has large windows for plenty of natural light. 3 bedrooms on the main level and all are great sized + the main flr has lrg bathroom w/jacuzzi tub! The 4th bedroom is in the finished basement, with the 2nd full bath and additional family room, great for entertaining. Laundry room has extra storage area and the oversized detached 2 car garage is just another plus to this home! Come see this one for yourself. WELCOME HOME!

Recently sold: $253,000. Whether it be the bright and spacious living and dining area or three bedrooms on one level, this home is move-in ready.   It has two bedrooms in the lower level in addition to unfinished space waiting to be completed - endless options!  This home's location gives you access to a variety of stores, restaurants, churches and great schools as well as family friendly parks, the Oval and Roseville Skating Center, gorgeous walking or biking trails and highways going any direction.  The furnace is 3-4 years old and the home has some newer windows.  Measurements to be verified by Buyer/Buyer's Agent.

description: Recently sold: $288,500. A CLEAN CLASSIC all brick and stone mid-century rambler on a fabulous 1/3 acre corner lot; tucked away in one of Roseville's top neighborhoods. Spacious and welcoming layout with 3 bedrooms on the main level, full bath, shared kitchen/dining with gorgeous bow window overlooking the south facing backyard and patio, and an elegant living room offering an oversized east facing picture window, cove ceiling, flagstone entry, and stacked stone wood burning fireplace! Expansive lower level family room with adjacent hobby/rec room and 1/2 bath. Charming open front porch, tons of space to play in the front, side and backyard, mature trees, beautiful gardens and perennials, double wide concrete driveway for extra parking, and a storage shed. Freshly painted main floor and exterior front and south peaks. Ultra convenient location to parks, many schools, Rosedale mall, local eats, bus line and Hwy 36 to either downtown.

description: Recently sold: $442,500. Are you ready to enjoy the summer on the patio in your beautiful garden?  Totally modern Roseville home, completely updated with a fabulous custom kitchen, extensive cabinetry,  granite, and (finally!) space for everything!  Hardwood floors throughout. All living facilities on one level including main floor master suite with built-in cabinetry and separate toilet and shower for busy working couples!  Fully tiled baths with marble, stone. Main floor laundry. Two blocks to Rosedale Mall.  Quick access to highways.  Short commute to both downtowns.  Award-winning Roseville schools.  Love golf?  Walk to the first tee.

Recently sold: $339,000. Multi level home with hardwood floors in dining room, living room, and hallway.  Ceramic tile floor in kitchen which was remodeled in 2005 with granite counters, dual fuel convection range, counter-depth refrigerator.  Designer colors on walls.

description: Recently sold: $341,000. Lovely, high-quality mid-century single story home offered for the first time in 49 years! May need some cosmetic updating. Over 3,000 finished sqft boasting of clean lines, hardwood floors, large kitchen over looking the in-ground private pool area. Two wood fireplaces for toasty winter evenings. Lots of windows to let in the sun from almost any room. Private master bath. Lower level office could serve as a fourth bedroom/ guest room conveniently located near a third 3/4 bath. Large family room in lower level to host large holiday or game watching events. In-ground pool and in ground sprinkler system on .38 acre lot. Conveniently tucked in a beautiful neighborhood just south of Hwy 36 & East of 280.SOLD- AS-IS.
Recently sold: $349,900.

Recently sold: $319,900. This 4-bedroom rambler style home has had the same owner for 48 years. There is lots of living space on the main floor including a large living room with wood-burning fireplace as well as a family room. All 4 bedrooms are on the main floor; fill them all up or use some for home office, nursery, den, or workout room. There is a nicely finished main floor full bathroom to go along with a convenient half-bathroom for guests. The kitchen opens to the family room and dining area. The home sits on a large, corner lot. There is an attached screened-in porch. the downstairs has another bathroom, a wonderful recreation room, and a sauna. Leave the basement for great storage and a workshop or look to finish and add square footage! With plenty of space inside & out, there's lots of room to entertain family & friends. Come & see all this home offers!
